Senate Banking Committee chairmanWilliam Proxmire, D-Wis, said Paul Volcker's decision to leavethe Federal Reserve Board was a loss for the country.    "I think it is a serious loss for the country," Proxmire saidin a Senate speech. He had no comment on the nomination of AlanGreespan to replace Volcker.    Proxmire's committee will hold confirmation hearings onGreenspan, but no date has been scheduled.    "Mr Volcker has been a superb chairman of the FederalReserve Board. He has the confidence of the business community.He has the confidence of the country. And I thought he had theconfidence of the Administration. We are going to miss him verymuch." Reuter&#3;